Version Devel - Jan 28, 2013 18:15

‘a,b’ Functions
  getA(expr) - returns real part of a complex number of form ‘a,b’
  getB(expr) - returns imaginary part
  N(a, b) - creates complex number ‘a,b’

Array Prototypes
  Array.addAll() - adds together all values of array using addr()

Other Functions
  checkArgs(name, args, ignore)
    - name is the name of the function calling it with the argument names
      - ex. "sin(z, nprec)"
    - args is the arguments object from the caller function
    - ignore is optional and is the number of arguments at the end that are optional
    - checks if the difference between the number of args and the number of args defined in the name is greater than the number of optional arguments
    - if so, throws an error
    - checkArgs ignores nprec argument
    - checks that nprec is real
  argsToArr(args)
    - used by checkArgs to convert arguments object into an array
  getNprec(nprec)
    - used by all complex functions to insure nprec is a number

Complex Functions
  - z and w are complex and x, y, n are real complex (getB(x) == "0")
  - nprec is the number of decimal digits to round to
  - when a function is multi-valued, the principal value is returned
  - a and b refer to the real and imaginary parts of z respectively
  
  add(z, w, nprec) - adds two complex numbers
  mult(z, w, nprec) - multiplies two complex numbers
  div(z, w, nprec) - divides two complex numbers
  exp(z, nprec) - exponential function; e to the power of z
  ln(z, nprec) - natural logarithm of z
  pow(z, w, nprec)
    - z to the power of w
    - if w = 1/n and n is odd, returns principal root
  root(n, z, nprec) - the nth root of z; if n is odd, returns real root
  sqrt(z, nprec) - the square root of z
  cbrt(z, nprec) - the cube root of z; uses root(3, z) so returns real cube root
  abs(z, nprec) - absolute value of z; sqrt(a^2+b^2)
  arg(z, nprec)
    - the argument of z
    - the angle from real axis to line formed from origin to z
    - uses atan2r(b, a) so range is [pi, -pi)
  sgn(z, nprec)
    - the point of intersection of the line passing through the origin and z and the unit circle
    - z/abs(z)
  sin(z, nprec) - the sine of z
  cos(z, nprec) - the cosine of z
  round(z, nprec) - rounds a and b to nprec
  trunc(z) - truncates a and b to 0 decimal places (ex. trunc(234.53) = 234)
  floor(z) - rounds a and b to nearest integer below it (ex. floor(34.999) = 34)
  ceil(z) - rounds a and b to nearest integer above it (ex. ceil(23.001) = 23)
  
